# Summary

**ChronicCopilot** is a personalized AI-driven chronic disease management system that solves fragmented, reactive healthcare by integrating real-time wearable data (CGM, smartwatch), medication schedules, and lab results into a closed-loop care platform. Rather than one-size-fits-all reminders, it builds a dynamic patient-specific baseline, applies dual-layer safety (clinical rules + ML anomaly detection), and delivers adaptive nudges at the right moment—escalating to clinicians via structured FHIR alerts before deterioration occurs.

The core novelty lies in orchestration: multimodal personalization across multiple chronic conditions, hybrid safety architecture, risk-trajectory-based escalation (not just threshold crossing), and reimbursement-native design that auto-captures RPM billing evidence. Built on FastAPI + FastMCP + PostgreSQL (+ TimescaleDB), the system exposes tools for anomaly detection, risk scoring, nudge generation, and FHIR task routing, enabling LLM agents to reason over patient safety constraints while remaining auditable and clinically accountable.

A 12-week MVP roadmap spans data integration, clinical guardrails, anomaly detection, patient copilot, care-team console, and pilot evaluation—targeting 3–4 chronic conditions (diabetes, hypertension, COPD) with measurable KPIs: fewer exacerbations, faster escalation, improved adherence, clean RPM claims, and low alert false-positive rates.

## One-line concept

Build a **personalized chronic care copilot** that watches each patient’s real-time health signals, gives the right daily action at the right moment, and safely escalates to clinicians before deterioration.

## Why this matters now

- Chronic disease drives most U.S. healthcare cost burden; CDC highlights chronic conditions as leading drivers of national spend ([CDC](https://www.cdc.gov/chronic-disease/data-research/facts-stats/)).
- Payment is shifting from “visits done” to “outcomes achieved” in value-based models ([CMS](https://www.cms.gov/newsroom/fact-sheets/better-care-smarter-spending-healthier-people-paying-providers-value-not-volume)).
- Remote monitoring is reimbursable today via RPM codes (`99453/99454/99457/99458`) if workflow/documentation is correct ([CMS RPM](https://www.cms.gov/medicare/coverage/telehealth/remote-patient-monitoring)).

## Current healthcare problems (what your invention should solve)

- Data is fragmented: CGM, smartwatch, meds, labs, and care plans sit in separate systems.
- Monitoring is reactive: care teams often detect issues after an ER visit or severe symptom.
